[Since no disease signs nor postmortem changes are included, this
apparently serious outbreak remains undiagnosed. A diagnosis is
urgently required, not only for animal-health sake but also to
exclude threats to public health (e.g., Rift valley fever, anthrax,
poisoning). Any additional information, particularly results of
veterinary investigations, is requested.

For the Monduli district, North Tanzania, bordering Kenya, see map at
<http://healthmap.org/r/00*u>. - Mod.AS]
